div.p:
The spherical triangles pAB, pAC, &c., will give us a simple rule. These
                    triangles are all right-angled at A, the side pA, equal to ZP, is the
                    co-latitude of the place, that is, the difference between the latitude and 90°;
                    and the successive angles ApB, ApC, &c. are 15°, 30°, &c., respectively.
                    Then tan. AB=tan. 15° sin. co-latitude;

